P value is 0.000217 which is less than 0.05. This mean, that we reject null hypothesis and accept alternate hypothesis.

Which indicates that our data is stationary .

SARIMAX Model¶

Now, we are implementing SARIMAX model by giving exogeneous variable to the model

Here, we are giving "page_loads" as exogenous variable

So, we are conidering SARIMA model for future predictions of Unique_visits.

Conclusion¶

We conclude that, Using SARIMAX model without exogenous, predicting for the next 2 months results in the downward trend as shown in the above plot with yellow marking.

The best results, we can observe from the all the deployed models is SARIMAX exogenous model. We have got very less RMSE score.
